# Text Idle - Core Rules (MANDATORY)

**Before ANY implementation, you MUST:**

1. [ ] Read `workflow.mdc` **Doc and Test Sync** and **Path → artifact triggers** for files you will touch
2. [ ] Confirm: Unit tests for changed logic; E2E when triggers in `workflow.mdc` require it (or N/A with reason)
3. [ ] Confirm: Will ALL code use ASCII only? (No Chinese in source)
4. [ ] Confirm: Which **docs and Examples** must move? (`docs/design/`, `docs/requirements-format.md`, `design-change-impact.md` per triggers)
5. [ ] Confirm: Final reply will include the **Sync summary** block (mandatory; see `workflow.mdc`)

---

## ASCII Encoding (STRICT - No Exceptions)

- Source code, comments, logs, tests, string literals, identifiers: **ASCII ONLY**
- Documentation (e.g. docs/*.md) may use non-ASCII
- If you see non-ASCII in code you edit: translate to English

---

## Definition of Done

A task is NOT complete until:

- Core logic has **unit tests** (frontend `*.spec.js` and/or Go `*_test.go` as applicable)
- Features with UI have **E2E tests** in `e2e/browser/` when the feature is user-visible
- **Documentation and requirements** stay aligned: if the change touches behavior, formulas, AC, or examples, update `docs/design/` and/or `docs/requirements-format.md` (and `docs/design-change-impact.md` when core flows change), or state **N/A** with reason
- The final response includes the **Sync summary** required by `workflow.mdc`
- All code is ASCII-only

---

## TDD / Test Requirements

- Prefer tests before implementation
- Unit tests: `frontend/src/**/*.spec.js` (Vitest)
- E2E tests: `e2e/browser/*.spec.js` (Playwright)
- Run: `npm run test` (frontend), `npm run e2e` (root)
